htw.vs1.filesystem

Class CommandParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • htw.vs1.filesystem.CommandParser

  • public class CommandParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Parses a Command-Argument-String. The words of the input string are divided by whitespace except the word is included in quotes. The first word is the command. The other words are the arguments. Created by felix on 20.06.15.

      • getArgs

        public java.lang.String[] getArgs()
        Gets the arguments of the input string. They are divided by whitespace except they are included in quotes.
        Returns:
        String array of the arguments.

      • getCommand

        public java.lang.String getCommand()
        Returns the command String of the parsed input. The command is the first string of the input divided by a whitespace from the rest of it.
        Returns:
        the command as a String or an empty String iff there is no command.
